President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Idaho due to flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from May 6 to June 16, 2017. This declaration allows federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Timothy B. Manner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.